{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went to see her every evening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one evening, when we got there, she wasn't there anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She'd died.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even her body wasn't there, far as we know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She died.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was on the 17th of January, 1945.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We really didn't know exactly what she died of.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, there were no death certificates, or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] She was almost 43, a few days short of 43 years old.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is the only time in the story where I get a bit upset and emotional, I'm sorry to say-- well, not sorry-- because we learned to live without-- without a mother.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was particularly difficult for Eve, of course, because she was now alone in her barracks, seven years old.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was taken on by an orthodox couple called the Birnbaums.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He apparently was a teacher, middle aged, forties, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he had six children of their own.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were very orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they took on orphans and other people like Eve, who'd lost their mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were all alone, really, because we couldn't look after her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Rudi, me, and my father were in another barrack.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the Birnbaums took on Eve after my mother died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And two months later, in March, the same thing happened to my father, really.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was taken ill.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He couldn't go to work anymore, so he was taken to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we visited him in-- in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And after a few days, he was gone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This is where I have a very difficult situation with you and your colleagues at one time, about did you forget to say goodbye-- one of your sessions that you had in Montreal, I think, or something like that, with the therapists.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
